**The coffee tree is a small tree, about 3 to 4 meters tall, with dense foliage and a relatively symmetrical shape. The coffee plant grows abundantly in the tropics and has small white flowers that are produced in clusters. These inflorescences will then develop into coffee berries, which are round or ovoid in shape and green when ripe. On the trunk of the coffee tree, many branches grow, creating a risky and diverse appearance for the tree.
